  "text": "The LLVM SelectionDAG type legalization system handles the error 'Cannot expand this type; LLVM lacks the right hooks' through multiple coordinated components: The main entry point is DAGTypeLegalizer::run() in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.cpp (lines 200-487), which drives the type legalization process. This function dispatches to type-specific handlers based on the type action determined by getTypeAction(). When a result type needs expansion (TypeExpandInteger or TypeExpandFloat), it calls ExpandIntegerResult() or ExpandFloatResult(). The ExpandIntegerResult() function in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp (starting at line 3024) contains a switch statement with a default case at lines 3034-3040 that issues a fatal error when encountering an unsupported operation: 'report_fatal_error(\"Do not know how to expand the result of this operator!\")'. This is the key location where expansion failures are detected and reported. The EVT (Extended Value Type) class defined in llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/ValueTypes.h (lines 35-139) provides the isSimple() method (lines 137-139) which tests whether a type is simple vs. extended. This method is crucial for type legalization validation. The DAGTypeLegalizer class, declared in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.h (line 31), orchestrates the entire type legalization process using internal maps for ExpandedIntegers and ExpandedFloats (lines 102, 118). The TargetLoweringBase::getTypeConversion() function in llvm/lib/CodeGen/TargetLoweringBase.cpp (lines 1329-1466) determines what legalization action to take for any given type, returning LegalizeKind enums that guide the expansion process. For extended types that cannot be legalized (e.g., extended float types), the system returns TypeExpandInteger or other expansion directives, which then flow to the expansion functions where unsupported cases trigger the fatal error. The LegalizeDAG class in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp handles operation-level legalization after type legalization completes."
}

